Young adult author Natalia Sylvester will be in conversation with bookstagrammer Carmen Alvarez about Sylvester’s new YA novel, “Breathe and Count Back From Ten,” at 6:30 p.m. July 19 at the Oxford Exchange, 420 W Kennedy Blvd., Tampa. Tickets $5 for admission or $19.34 for admission plus a copy of the book at oxfordexchange.com/pages/calendar. Book Talk is a listing of in-person author appearances in the Tampa Bay area in the coming week. To place an item in Book Talk, send author’s name, book title, appearance time, date, venue name and address, admission cost (if any) and a contact phone number to cbancroft@tampabay.com, with “Book Talk” in the subject line. Deadline is 14 days before publication.